codex
The patch introduces false negatives for filterable attributes on edge-body search hits, and it also changes a public Rust struct in a source-breaking way. These issues should be addressed before considering the patch correct.

Full review comments:

- [P2] Populate edge attributes before enforcing filters — /home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb-worktrees/orch-0.8.20-s15b/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:10099-10106
  When an attribute filter is applied to an edge-body hit, this new check reads `canonical_attributes`, but that table is only populated from canonical node bodies (`project_node_attributes` / `backfill_attribute` iterate `canonical_nodes`). As a result, an edge whose body contains the matching filterable attribute, e.g. `{"priority":"high"}`, is rejected by the FTS arm because the lookup falls back to the empty sentinel; the vector insert path has the same edge-body gap by reading only `canonical_nodes` for attr values. Edge attribute filters therefore produce false negatives for valid edge hits.

- [P2] Avoid breaking public SearchFilter literals — /home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb-worktrees/orch-0.8.20-s15b/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:2460-2473
  Adding a required public field to the re-exported `SearchFilter` breaks downstream Rust callers that construct the existing four-field struct literal without `..Default::default()`. Since this is a governed public surface, callers compiling against the base branch will now fail to compile unless the API change is intentionally documented/versioned or exposed through a backwards-compatible construction path.
