- [P2] Avoid breaking public SearchFilter literals — /home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb-worktrees/orch-0.8.20-s15b/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:2460-2473
  Adding a required public field to the re-exported `SearchFilter` breaks downstream Rust callers that construct the existing four-field struct literal without `..Default::default()`. Since this is a governed public surface, callers compiling against the base branch will now fail to compile unless the API change is intentionally documented/versioned or exposed through a backwards-compatible construction path.
